--- a/drivers/bluetooth/btusb.c
+++ b/drivers/bluetooth/btusb.c
@@ ... @@ static const struct usb_device_id btusb_table[] = {
 	/* Fake CSR clone - CSR8510 A10 */
-	{ USB_DEVICE(0x10d7, 0xb012), .driver_info = BTUSB_ACTIONS_SEMI },
+	{ USB_DEVICE(0x10d7, 0xb012), .driver_info = BTUSB_CSR }, /* Fake CSR clone - CSR8510 A10 */

The kernel already has 10d7:b012 in the device table but marks it as
BTUSB_ACTIONS_SEMI (Actions Semiconductor). This is wrong for the
CSR8510 A10 clone — it needs BTUSB_CSR so firmware upload happens.
